{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The node owner. A node can have any ancestor node as owner (i.e. a parent, grandparent, etc. node ascending in the tree). This implies that "},{"code":"addChild(node:forceReadableName:`internal`:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" should be called before setting the owner, so that this relationship of parenting exists. When saving a node (using "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"), all the nodes it owns will be saved with it. This allows for the creation of complex scene trees, with instancing and subinstancing."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"]]},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"owner"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Node","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC5ownerACSgvp","title":"owner"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node\/owner"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/owner","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"owner"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Node","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC"},{"kind":"text","text":"? { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want a child to be persisted to a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene"},{"type":"text","text":", you must set "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/owner","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" in addition to calling "},{"code":"addChild(node:forceReadableName:`internal`:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This is typically relevant for [url=$DOCS_URL\/tutorials\/plugins\/running_code_in_the_editor.html]tool scripts[\/url] and [url=$DOCS_URL\/tutorials\/plugins\/editor\/index.html]editor plugins[\/url]. If a new node is added to the tree without setting its owner as an ancestor in that tree, it will be visible in the 2D\/3D view, but not in the scene tree (and not persisted when packing or saving).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Node"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Node","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","role":"symbol","title":"Node","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Base class for all scene objects."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/PackedScene":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PackedScene"}],"title":"PackedScene","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/packedscene","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"An abstraction of a serialized scene.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PackedScene"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node/owner":{"title":"owner","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node\/owner","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"owner","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Node","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot4NodeC"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/owner","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The node owner. A node can have any ancestor node as owner (i.e. a parent, grandparent, etc. node ascending in the tree). This implies that ","type":"text"},{"code":"addChild(node:forceReadableName:`internal`:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" should be called before setting the owner, so that this relationship of parenting exists. When saving a node (using "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedScene","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"), all the nodes it owns will be saved with it. This allows for the creation of complex scene trees, with instancing and subinstancing."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","title":"SwiftGodot","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"}}}